Detailed Description

The muse namespace.

Everything in the api is in the muse namespace.

Typedef Documentation

typedef set<Agent> muse::AgentContainer

The AgentContainer.

Holds a collection of agents, this is basically a set of Agents. Always use the AgentContainer type, because the underlying implamentation could change.

typedef struct AgentIDType muse::AgentID [read]

The AgentID struct.

This is used to store the id of an agent. muse uses this AgentID struct to make sure the client know exactly what the param of a method is asking for. For more details check out the method Agent::getAgentID().

See also:
getAgentID()

typedef std::set<Event> muse::EventContainer

The EventContainer.

Holds a collection of events, this is basically a set of Events. Always use the EventContainer type, because the underlying implamentation could change.

enum muse::TimeType

The Enum TimeType.

When retrieveing the simulation time you must pass in a TimeType, by default TimeType = NOW.
